15:04.642 --> 15:06.688
- Feel the burn?
- [breathes heavily]

15:06.731 --> 15:09.952
Everywhere.
You're kicking my ass.

15:09.996 --> 15:11.562
- That's my job.

15:21.224 --> 15:22.660
[door closes]

15:25.272 --> 15:27.709
- Mm.
- He out?

15:27.752 --> 15:29.058
- One song, two books,

15:29.102 --> 15:31.495
and a dissertation
on velociraptors.

15:33.236 --> 15:35.151
- You think
he talks too much?

15:35.195 --> 15:36.761
- Um, have you met the boy?

15:36.805 --> 15:38.285
- I mean, like, in general.

15:38.328 --> 15:40.069
- Kid's a damn chatterbox.

15:42.332 --> 15:44.726
- He doesn't lose stuff,
does he?

15:44.769 --> 15:47.468
- Well...
he lost that blue jacket.

15:47.511 --> 15:49.165
- But then he found it.

15:49.209 --> 15:52.386
- Yeah, but then
he lost the hat.

15:52.429 --> 15:54.692
- You think he does that
occasionally,

15:54.736 --> 15:56.346
often, or very often?

15:56.390 --> 15:58.566
- What are you doing?

15:58.609 --> 16:01.221
- There's a prelim form
to fill out.

16:01.264 --> 16:02.700
- He doesn't need a test, Ruby.

16:02.744 --> 16:04.789
- You heard what she said.
- You know what I heard?

16:04.833 --> 16:06.574
That his white teacher
can't tell the difference

16:06.617 --> 16:08.837
between an energetic kid
and a misbehaving Black boy.

16:08.880 --> 16:11.274
- What if it's not just that?

16:11.318 --> 16:14.582
- What else would it be?
- Us.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.236
- What, like, we gave him ADHD?

16:16.279 --> 16:17.411
- We dropped the ball.

16:17.454 --> 16:20.414
- I thought
that was with Sara.

16:20.457 --> 16:22.024
- Could be both of them.

16:24.635 --> 16:26.594
- Mm-mm.
Ain't nothing wrong with him.

16:26.637 --> 16:27.638
And I don't need some test

16:27.682 --> 16:29.684
to tell me how I'm doing
as a father.

16:39.694 --> 16:41.000
- Look,
installation's free.

16:41.043 --> 16:43.176
I'm gonna send my guys
over to your backyard.

16:43.219 --> 16:44.612
They're gonna turn it
into paradise.

16:44.655 --> 16:46.222
You're never gonna
want to leave!

16:46.266 --> 16:47.354
- Welcome to Boland Bubbles,

16:47.397 --> 16:49.921
where we
"tropic" like it's hot.

16:49.965 --> 16:53.012
[upbeat music playing
over speakers]

16:53.055 --> 16:56.841
♪

16:56.885 --> 16:58.234
- Hi.

16:58.278 --> 17:00.236
If you have any questions,
I'd be happy to help.

17:00.280 --> 17:03.587
- Y'all under new management?
- Family owned and operated.

17:03.631 --> 17:05.111
- Looks different.
[laughs]

17:05.154 --> 17:07.374
- Out with the old,
in with the new, right?

17:07.417 --> 17:08.636
- New paint!
- Yeah!

17:08.679 --> 17:10.072
And lots of new inventory.

17:10.116 --> 17:12.596
I'm Beth, by the way.
- Terry.

17:12.640 --> 17:14.685
Tell me about this bad boy.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.644
- Oh, you've got a good eye.
- [laughs]

17:16.687 --> 17:18.820
- This is our Insignia X5--

17:18.863 --> 17:21.823
35 jets, individual seating.

17:21.866 --> 17:25.261
Comes in bronze, walnut,
and sandstone.

17:25.305 --> 17:26.393
- Mm.

17:26.436 --> 17:28.569
♪

17:28.612 --> 17:31.441
What kind of voltage
does she pull?

17:31.485 --> 17:34.488
- Uh...standard outlet?

17:34.531 --> 17:36.577
Just plug and play.

17:36.620 --> 17:38.144
- Where's the
little girl's room?

17:38.187 --> 17:39.667
Got to tinkle.

17:39.710 --> 17:41.321
- Uh, just there on the left.

17:41.364 --> 17:43.627
♪

17:43.671 --> 17:45.760
- Great turnout, right?
It's crazy!

17:45.803 --> 17:47.979
- I'm trying to close an X5.

17:48.023 --> 17:49.546
- Nice!

17:49.590 --> 17:51.026
♪

17:51.070 --> 17:53.246
- Ooh.
Heads up, that was fast.

17:53.289 --> 17:54.725
- [clears throat]

17:54.769 --> 17:57.163
- Well, Terry, you seem
to know your way around a spa.

17:57.206 --> 17:59.426
So I would love to introduce
you to my husband

17:59.469 --> 18:01.689
and have him walk you through
some of the technical features

18:01.732 --> 18:02.864
and see what you think.

18:02.907 --> 18:05.519
- I think you're shut down.

18:05.562 --> 18:06.868
- I'm sorry?

18:06.911 --> 18:09.131
- I'm a building inspector
with Wayne County.

18:09.175 --> 18:12.352
You folks got yourself
a load of violations.

18:12.395 --> 18:17.748
♪

18:17.792 --> 18:19.968
Painted over
your sprinkler heads.

18:20.011 --> 18:22.188
Gonna have to dock you on that.

18:22.231 --> 18:25.234
[upbeat jazzy music playing
over speakers]

18:25.278 --> 18:28.542
Got a residential power strip
juicing all your units.

18:28.585 --> 18:30.152
Got to dock ya!

18:30.196 --> 18:32.067
♪

18:32.111 --> 18:34.287
Centerline of the toilet
in your tinkler

18:34.330 --> 18:36.898
is less than 15 inches
from this wall.

18:36.941 --> 18:39.422
That's a two-fer--
plumbing and ADA.

18:39.466 --> 18:41.207
So what do I got to do, Dean?

18:41.250 --> 18:44.123
- Dock me?
- Mm-hmm.

18:44.166 --> 18:45.646
♪

18:45.689 --> 18:50.607
So that's sprinklers, wiring,
construction, plumbing.

18:50.651 --> 18:54.307
- This could take months.
- If you're lucky.

18:54.350 --> 18:56.526
Can I get another one of these
for my niece?

18:56.570 --> 18:57.919
♪

18:57.962 --> 19:00.443
- Yeah, a-at the front.

19:00.487 --> 19:01.792
- All right, folks!

19:01.836 --> 19:04.012
That's a wrap
on Boland Bubbles.

19:04.055 --> 19:07.189
Don't have to go home,
but you can't stay here.

19:07.233 --> 19:11.150
♪

19:12.760 --> 19:13.152
.

19:13.195 --> 19:15.197
- All right, ladies.
Now pick up those buns.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.677
No slacking.
Let's go.

19:16.720 --> 19:18.635
- It's like a friends
and family discount.

19:18.679 --> 19:19.810
- I didn't know
y'all were open.

19:19.854 --> 19:21.160
- Oh, we're not.

19:21.203 --> 19:24.163
But, you know, you guys are,
like, tastemakers.

19:24.206 --> 19:25.816
I'm telling you...

19:25.860 --> 19:28.776
once you step foot
in the hot and steamy Boland,

19:28.819 --> 19:32.127
you will not be able
to keep it a secret.

19:32.171 --> 19:34.564
- We just put in a new deck.

19:34.608 --> 19:37.524
- Well, you know what goes
with a new deck.

19:37.567 --> 19:40.004
- Lily just started
private school.

19:40.048 --> 19:41.267
We can't afford it.

19:41.310 --> 19:43.225
- I'm not even supposed
to be selling them.

19:43.269 --> 19:44.922
I'll work with you.

19:44.966 --> 19:48.361
- Less mouth, more ass.

19:48.404 --> 19:49.971
- [whispering]
I have brochures.

19:50.014 --> 19:51.233
- You got to breathe!

19:51.277 --> 19:53.583
You want to stop peeing
when you sneeze?

19:53.627 --> 19:56.195
- You can just pick 'em up
and pass 'em out at drop-off.

19:56.238 --> 19:59.110
- Tuck your butts!

19:59.154 --> 20:01.243
- I'll hook anybody up.

20:01.287 --> 20:04.507
[hip-hop music playing]

20:04.551 --> 20:06.596
- Selling hot tubs
in my class?

20:06.640 --> 20:09.599
- [breathing heavily]
Sorry.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.775
♪

20:11.819 --> 20:14.474
- Do I count as
friend and family?

20:14.517 --> 20:15.953
- Uh...

20:15.997 --> 20:17.041
yeah, sure.

20:17.085 --> 20:19.740
- How low can you go?

20:19.783 --> 20:21.132
I mean pricing.

20:21.176 --> 20:22.656
- Oh.

20:22.699 --> 20:23.918
Um...

20:25.224 --> 20:29.097
Lower than my pelvic floor
after four kids.

20:29.140 --> 20:30.838
- You take Venmo?

20:30.881 --> 20:32.405
- I'll take anything.

20:32.448 --> 20:35.146
[breathing heavily]

20:35.190 --> 20:37.236
♪

20:43.329 --> 20:45.809
- Hey.
- [sighs] Hey.

20:45.853 --> 20:47.985
- Where's Ben?

20:48.029 --> 20:49.204
- Cleaning the house.

20:49.248 --> 20:51.859
- Alone?
Why?

20:51.902 --> 20:53.948
- We need to talk about him.

20:53.991 --> 20:56.211
- [sighs]

20:58.126 --> 20:59.475
It's not cool, right?

20:59.519 --> 21:02.261
- He told you?
- [sighs]

21:02.304 --> 21:04.306
[door closes]

21:04.350 --> 21:05.655
What do we do?
- I don't know.

21:05.699 --> 21:09.572
Nancy thinks we should
make him switch schools.

21:09.616 --> 21:12.358
- Yeah, I mean,
maybe she's right.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.273
- Over one party?

21:14.316 --> 21:15.970
- Huh?

21:16.013 --> 21:19.016
- Didn't the cops call you?

21:19.060 --> 21:20.279
- What are you talking about?

21:20.322 --> 21:22.150
- Ben threw a rager
at our house.

21:22.193 --> 21:23.673
- Well, where the hell
were you?

21:23.717 --> 21:26.110
- We were just
at Nancy's parents' cabin.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.112
What did you think
we were talking about?

21:28.156 --> 21:30.289
- That he has no friends.
- [laughs]

21:30.332 --> 21:32.769
He had, like, 100 people
at our house.

21:32.813 --> 21:34.031
- Who?

21:34.075 --> 21:36.077
- Sam, Eddie, Janice,
the whole lacrosse team.

21:36.120 --> 21:38.209
I don't know,
the usual suspects.

21:38.253 --> 21:39.950
- I don't know
any of those suspects.

21:39.994 --> 21:42.257
- Okay, well, they all had
their shoes on in our house,

21:42.301 --> 21:43.954
and Nancy is losing her mind.

21:51.092 --> 21:52.615
- He plays lacrosse?

21:52.659 --> 21:54.225
- Yeah.
How do you not know that?

21:54.269 --> 21:58.317
- How did you know that?
- 'Cause I bought him the gear.

21:58.360 --> 22:00.710
- [sighs]

22:00.754 --> 22:03.234
- Sorry, look,
you've been really busy.

22:03.278 --> 22:05.106
- That's not why.

22:05.149 --> 22:07.108
- W-we just know
all the parents

22:07.151 --> 22:09.502
around the neighborhood
and stuff.

22:09.545 --> 22:11.982
- And lacrosse.

22:12.026 --> 22:13.288
- Don't go there.

22:13.332 --> 22:14.898
- Already there.

22:16.987 --> 22:19.555
- He just knows you wouldn't
really be into it.

22:19.599 --> 22:23.907
- What? His whole new secret,
fancy life?

22:25.387 --> 22:26.823
- Well...

22:26.867 --> 22:29.435
he's got a game next weekend
if you want to come.

22:29.478 --> 22:32.829
You could meet
all the usual suspects.

22:36.746 --> 22:39.967
- Can I borrow something
from Nancy to wear?

22:40.010 --> 22:43.013
- No, your boobs are too big.
[both chuckle]

22:46.147 --> 22:48.758
- We would love for you to take
another look at our facility.

22:48.802 --> 22:51.761
- You couldn't have possibly
fixed everything that fast.

22:51.805 --> 22:54.764
- Well, we came up
with some creative solutions.

22:54.808 --> 22:57.114
- Well, I've been doing this
for 19 years,

22:57.158 --> 22:59.203
and, believe me,
I've seen it all.

22:59.247 --> 23:01.380
[chuckles]
- Have you seen this?

23:01.423 --> 23:03.469
- Looks the same.

23:03.512 --> 23:05.122
Are you trying
to waste my time?

23:05.166 --> 23:09.083
- Um, we're...trying...

23:09.126 --> 23:11.346
to make it worth your while.

23:15.655 --> 23:17.918
- [clears throat]
Yes, uh...

23:17.961 --> 23:21.704
we know how, uh,
how tricky wiring can be.

23:21.748 --> 23:23.445
So please just let us know

23:23.489 --> 23:26.143
if there's anything
you'd like us to do.

23:26.187 --> 23:27.623
- And, obviously,

23:27.667 --> 23:29.886
we can't knock down
the whole tinkler.

23:29.930 --> 23:32.411
[laughs]
So we...

23:32.454 --> 23:34.151
got a new toilet.

23:34.195 --> 23:36.763
- We haven't installed it yet.

23:36.806 --> 23:39.156
What do you, uh--
what do you think?

23:39.200 --> 23:40.854
- Did we pass?

23:42.986 --> 23:45.162
- [breathes deeply]

23:45.206 --> 23:47.208
[mid-tempo music playing]

23:47.251 --> 23:49.036
♪

23:49.079 --> 23:53.127
[door opens and closes]

23:53.170 --> 23:57.566
♪

23:57.610 --> 23:59.089
- Buy you a drink?

23:59.133 --> 24:00.830
- I own the place.

24:00.874 --> 24:03.354
♪

24:03.398 --> 24:05.313
- Well, why don't you
buy me one, then?

24:05.356 --> 24:07.402
- Why would I do that?

24:07.446 --> 24:10.013
- Boland Bubbles
is in business.

24:10.057 --> 24:11.580
♪

24:11.624 --> 24:13.669
- That's what he's calling it?

24:13.713 --> 24:14.931
- Yeah, I think it's cute.

24:14.975 --> 24:17.891
- Yeah.
Real panty-dropper.

24:17.934 --> 24:19.849
♪

24:19.893 --> 24:21.938
- Yeah, well,
it's fully operational.

24:21.982 --> 24:24.288
Your money is being cleaned,
laundered, folded,

24:24.332 --> 24:26.726
and pressed as we speak.

24:26.769 --> 24:29.903
Um, a tequila for the chief.

24:29.946 --> 24:31.861
Top shelf.

24:31.905 --> 24:33.950
And, um...

24:35.212 --> 24:38.389
Do you have anything
without alcohol or caffeine?

24:38.433 --> 24:43.394
♪

24:43.438 --> 24:46.006
Just bourbon, neat.

24:46.049 --> 24:52.969
♪

24:57.583 --> 24:59.019
Could be more excited.

24:59.062 --> 25:01.456
- It ain't always
about you, is it?

25:01.500 --> 25:02.936
- It's what you wanted!

25:02.979 --> 25:06.069
- You know what?
I got other stuff on my mind.

25:06.113 --> 25:07.854
- I need that gun.

25:07.897 --> 25:12.293
♪

25:12.336 --> 25:13.947
- I'm sorry, what?

25:13.990 --> 25:15.557
♪

25:15.601 --> 25:17.428
- We're up and running,

25:17.472 --> 25:20.170
I'm making you bank.

25:20.214 --> 25:23.260
Doesn't make sense to hold it
over me anymore.

25:23.304 --> 25:25.088
♪

25:25.132 --> 25:27.090
- You know what?

25:27.134 --> 25:29.963
♪

25:30.006 --> 25:31.921
You're right.

25:31.965 --> 25:35.534
♪

25:35.577 --> 25:37.361
- I am?

25:37.405 --> 25:38.798
- Yeah.

25:38.841 --> 25:40.930
I'm not gonna hold it
over you anymore.

25:40.974 --> 25:43.933
♪

25:43.977 --> 25:46.327
- Thanks.

25:46.370 --> 25:48.155
- Cops might, though.

25:48.198 --> 25:51.462
♪

25:51.506 --> 25:53.769
Yeah, see, the lawyer says

25:53.813 --> 25:56.380
I got to go in
about that friend of yours.

25:56.424 --> 26:00.123
♪

26:00.167 --> 26:02.169
Apparently they think
I had something to do with it,

26:02.212 --> 26:03.910
which is just crazy.

26:03.953 --> 26:06.608
♪

26:06.652 --> 26:09.306
[chuckles]

26:09.350 --> 26:11.134
- And what are you gonna
tell 'em?

26:11.178 --> 26:13.093
♪

26:13.136 --> 26:15.486
- I'm not sure I got to say
anything.

26:15.530 --> 26:19.316
♪

26:19.360 --> 26:20.535
- If you give it to them,

26:20.579 --> 26:22.885
I'm not the only thing
that goes away.

26:22.929 --> 26:25.584
♪

26:25.627 --> 26:28.021
- Mm-hmm.

26:28.064 --> 26:30.153
Priorities, huh?

26:30.197 --> 26:37.117
♪

26:39.598 --> 26:41.425
- I'll take another one.

26:41.469 --> 26:44.733
♪

26:49.433 --> 26:49.608
.

26:49.651 --> 26:51.305
- There's a one-way
to St. Petersburg.

26:51.348 --> 26:52.654
Leaves at midnight.

26:52.698 --> 26:54.656
- Florida?
- Russia.

26:54.700 --> 26:55.918
- Why Russia?

26:55.962 --> 26:57.311
- Because they'll
give you asylum.

26:57.354 --> 26:59.356
- How do you even know
he's gonna turn over the gun?

26:59.400 --> 27:01.663
- How do I know he's not?
- Exactly.

27:01.707 --> 27:02.969
It's why we got to get your ass
on this plane

27:03.012 --> 27:04.884
to Sheremetyevo Airport, now.

27:04.927 --> 27:07.364
- She's gonna live
in Russia now?

27:07.408 --> 27:10.106
- Yeah, I mean, Snowden
lived in the terminal.

27:10.150 --> 27:11.673
- Her kids?

27:11.717 --> 27:13.327
- We'll sneak 'em out
one by one.

27:13.370 --> 27:15.808
- So it's gonna be
one big happy family

27:15.851 --> 27:17.940
living in a terminal.

27:17.984 --> 27:19.289
- Snowden did.

27:19.333 --> 27:21.335
- Eating Sbarro's.
- Snowden did.

27:21.378 --> 27:23.163
- 'Cause they have Sbarro's
in Russia?

27:23.206 --> 27:24.860
- Since 1997.

27:24.904 --> 27:26.122
The point is,

27:26.166 --> 27:27.950
you can't be extradited
for murder.

27:27.994 --> 27:30.039
- You just need a lawyer.

27:31.388 --> 27:33.739
- I was the last person
she was seen with.

27:33.782 --> 27:35.001
- Okay, a good one.

27:35.044 --> 27:36.742
- And I lied to the police.

27:36.785 --> 27:38.961
- A real good one.
- And I stole her bird.

27:39.005 --> 27:40.267
- Technically,
I stole her bird.

27:40.310 --> 27:41.964
- Okay, where's her
power-walking boyfriend?

27:42.008 --> 27:43.052
He'll back you up.

27:43.096 --> 27:44.271
- He's probably
still in diapers

27:44.314 --> 27:45.881
since the last time
he saw gang friend.

27:45.925 --> 27:48.275
- You didn't pull the trigger.

27:48.318 --> 27:50.799
- I may as well have.

27:56.936 --> 27:59.721
- What are you looking for?

27:59.765 --> 28:01.767
She's making me mental.

28:06.249 --> 28:09.992
[Adult's "Nite Life"]

28:10.036 --> 28:11.602
- Dear Dean,

28:11.646 --> 28:14.170
I've spent the last two years
cooking and cleaning.

28:14.214 --> 28:18.566
I've learned I'm excellent at
both, and you will be, too...

28:18.609 --> 28:20.699
because I'm going to tell you
exactly what to do

28:20.742 --> 28:22.701
and how to do it.

28:22.744 --> 28:24.485
My friends will make
the money.

28:24.528 --> 28:28.576
You're gonna buy hot tubs
with it, a lot of 'em,

28:28.619 --> 28:32.058
from as many wholesalers
as you can, just in case.

28:32.101 --> 28:33.233
Spread it around.

28:33.276 --> 28:35.235
This is where you shine, Dean.

28:35.278 --> 28:37.977
Price doesn't matter.
It's all profit.

28:38.020 --> 28:39.892
Now you're gonna sell 'em.

28:39.935 --> 28:43.504
♪

28:43.547 --> 28:46.333
And this is how you hide it.

28:46.376 --> 28:47.856
Inflate the sales price

28:47.900 --> 28:49.945
or the number
of the units sold,

28:49.989 --> 28:51.425
ideally both.

28:51.468 --> 28:53.427
It's pretty simple.

28:53.470 --> 28:55.168
I know you can do this.

28:55.211 --> 28:56.996
You can still live the dream.

28:57.039 --> 28:59.825
Nobody needs to know
how you got there.

28:59.868 --> 29:03.437
Love, Beth.

29:03.480 --> 29:06.701
- ♪ In my night life,
I don't think twice ♪

29:06.745 --> 29:10.052
♪ Everything is so nice

29:10.096 --> 29:13.447
♪ Loving the luxury
of the night life ♪

29:13.490 --> 29:16.667
♪ Everything is all right

29:16.711 --> 29:20.106
♪ Blinded by the headlights,
driving past midnight ♪

29:20.149 --> 29:23.457
♪ Looks like a still life

29:23.500 --> 29:25.198
♪ Give me something cheap

29:25.241 --> 29:26.939
♪ Not enough sleep

29:26.982 --> 29:28.549
♪ Which one do I keep?

29:28.592 --> 29:30.290
♪ You or my night life?

29:30.333 --> 29:37.471
♪

29:44.870 --> 29:46.959
- Remember when those raccoons
tracked the mud

29:47.002 --> 29:48.743
all over the downspout?

29:48.787 --> 29:51.224
♪

29:51.267 --> 29:54.401
- I need to tell you
something.

29:54.444 --> 29:57.012
- Look at this--I have
to repaint the entire door.

29:57.056 --> 29:58.274
And it's all over,

29:58.318 --> 30:00.102
everywhere that inspector
woman touched!

30:00.146 --> 30:02.844
I have to redo the bathroom,
the front area over there.

30:02.888 --> 30:04.541
It's, like, what?
Did she change the oil

30:04.585 --> 30:06.717
on her car
before she came here?

30:06.761 --> 30:09.372
And Eric, I mean, he's already
returned the stuff,

30:09.416 --> 30:10.678
and we're never gonna match
the color.

30:10.721 --> 30:13.855
I mean, it's Swiss coffee
and pale avocado.

30:13.899 --> 30:17.380
[continues indistinctly]

30:17.424 --> 30:19.992
[Muzak playing]

30:20.035 --> 30:21.689
Hey.

30:23.386 --> 30:25.214
What do you want to tell me?

30:27.042 --> 30:28.739
- Nothing.

30:33.309 --> 30:35.442
[door closes]

30:35.485 --> 30:37.661
- Stopped by the school today.

30:37.705 --> 30:39.011
- What for?

30:39.054 --> 30:40.577
- Tell little man's principal
that if Ms. Jackson

30:40.621 --> 30:42.231
can't take an honest fart joke,

30:42.275 --> 30:45.887
then maybe our son's
not the problem.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.193
- How'd that go over?

30:47.236 --> 30:50.544
- He starts in Ms. V's class
on Monday.

30:50.587 --> 30:52.720
Bad people,
not bad parents.

30:53.764 --> 30:56.942
- What happens when he does
the same thing in her class?

30:56.985 --> 30:59.727
- Well, she sees kids as kids.

30:59.770 --> 31:01.076
- Mm.

31:01.120 --> 31:03.557
- What's this?
- [pops lips] Science homework.

31:03.600 --> 31:06.560
- He didn't do it?
- Oh, he did it.

31:06.603 --> 31:08.431
- Why did he draw
a picture of a cactus?

31:08.475 --> 31:09.606
- It's not a cactus.

31:09.650 --> 31:11.391
- Meerkat?
- Nope.

31:11.434 --> 31:13.784
- Prairie dog?
- Penis.

31:15.699 --> 31:16.918
Math.

31:18.702 --> 31:20.487
- I'm guessing
this is not a number.

31:20.530 --> 31:22.054
- And history.

31:22.097 --> 31:23.707
- [gasps]

31:23.751 --> 31:25.231
- I'm gonna
get ahead of this one

31:25.274 --> 31:26.362
and let you know right now,

31:26.406 --> 31:30.018
it's not
the Washington Monument.

31:30.062 --> 31:31.933
- I was really hoping it was.

31:33.979 --> 31:34.980
- Me too.

31:36.982 --> 31:39.593
- Uh-uh-uh.

31:39.636 --> 31:42.726
I'll call
about the test tomorrow.

31:48.036 --> 31:51.039
[man speaking indistinctly
on TV]

31:57.263 --> 31:59.613
- Hey.
- Hi.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.745
[door closes]
- How was Dad's?

32:01.789 --> 32:02.877
- Boring.

32:02.921 --> 32:04.748
- How was the dinner?
- Plant-based.

32:04.792 --> 32:07.012
Um, I got homework, so...

32:07.055 --> 32:08.622
- Hey.
I thought...

32:08.665 --> 32:12.060
maybe next weekend we could,
like, go to the movies?

32:12.104 --> 32:14.628
You know, buy one ticket
and then sneak into five?

32:14.671 --> 32:16.282
- I think I might go
to Dad's again.

32:16.325 --> 32:18.284
- You were just there.

32:18.327 --> 32:20.112
- I know, but I have
a school thing.

32:20.155 --> 32:21.287
- Oh.

32:21.330 --> 32:23.158
Sick.
Can I come?

32:23.202 --> 32:26.640
- It's sort of
not for parents.

32:29.991 --> 32:32.515
- Yeah, no, that's--that's
totally cool.

32:32.559 --> 32:35.910
- But I'm still totally down
for the movie thing.

32:35.954 --> 32:37.346
- Hey, Ben?

32:40.828 --> 32:42.047
Happy birthday.

32:42.090 --> 32:43.744
- Thanks.

32:46.007 --> 32:48.053
[door closes]

33:02.806 --> 33:04.852
- Sure you don't want a fork?

33:04.895 --> 33:06.854
- Mm-mm.

33:06.897 --> 33:09.378
- Just thought it might be
a little more...

33:09.422 --> 33:12.860
efficient
for your, uh...

33:12.903 --> 33:14.557
situation.

33:14.601 --> 33:16.733
- What do you want?

33:21.260 --> 33:23.436
- Do you got kids?

33:25.394 --> 33:28.484
- Got a little girl
in Cincinnati.

33:28.528 --> 33:31.792
- You get to see her at all?

33:31.835 --> 33:35.187
- I try to get there
for her birthdays.

33:35.230 --> 33:37.145
- That sucks.

33:37.189 --> 33:41.454
- She's got a good mom.
It's better this way.

33:47.068 --> 33:48.722
- I need a favor.

33:48.765 --> 33:52.421
- [scoffs]
You sound like your sister.

33:54.293 --> 33:56.947
- She's a really good mom, too.

33:56.991 --> 33:59.167
- So?

34:04.781 --> 34:08.089
- So it really shouldn't be
her prints on that gun.

34:22.669 --> 34:24.932
- Dumpling?

34:51.045 --> 34:51.219
.

34:51.263 --> 34:52.655
[engine stops, car door opens]

35:04.363 --> 35:06.321
- [sniffs]

35:18.290 --> 35:21.293
- When are you going in?
- Soon.

35:25.514 --> 35:27.473
- I've been thinking
a lot about it.

35:27.516 --> 35:29.475
- I'll bet you have.

35:31.607 --> 35:35.045
- It's hard to wrap your
brain around, actually...

35:35.089 --> 35:36.264
that each of our fingerprints

35:36.308 --> 35:39.267
is totally
and completely unique.

35:40.703 --> 35:42.183
Snowflakes too.

35:42.227 --> 35:43.967
And tiger stripes.

35:44.011 --> 35:45.447
Like, why?

35:45.491 --> 35:46.927
- Don't know,

35:46.970 --> 35:49.364
but it really works out
in my favor.

35:51.018 --> 35:52.672
- Does it?

35:58.547 --> 36:00.462
Forgot one.

36:00.506 --> 36:02.160
- What's this?

36:02.203 --> 36:03.726
- You can keep it.

36:05.380 --> 36:08.514
I've got the original
somewhere safe.

36:21.091 --> 36:23.920
Just crazy...

36:23.964 --> 36:28.142
that there's
a way to get everyone...

36:28.186 --> 36:30.405
even tigers.

36:37.412 --> 36:40.067
Let me know what the cops say.

36:44.680 --> 36:46.421
- Is that booze?

36:47.901 --> 36:49.250
- This boy

36:49.294 --> 36:52.427
has worked a penis
into almost every one of these.

36:59.086 --> 37:03.569
- [sighs]
What did the specialist say?

37:03.612 --> 37:06.006
- You're probably gonna
want some of this.

37:06.049 --> 37:08.574
- It's that bad?
- It's pretty bad.

37:08.617 --> 37:11.011
- [sighs]
Like special-school bad?

37:11.054 --> 37:12.142
- Mm-hmm.

37:12.186 --> 37:14.275
The real expensive kind.

37:24.111 --> 37:26.113
- This says he should be
in eighth grade.

37:26.156 --> 37:27.941
- Yep.

37:27.984 --> 37:29.421
- But he's in second grade.

37:30.770 --> 37:32.511
- Yeah.

37:34.774 --> 37:36.297
- No.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.647
- Boy's a damn genius.

37:42.869 --> 37:45.045
- What are we gonna do?

37:45.088 --> 37:47.308
- How are we gonna afford
that school?

37:50.355 --> 37:52.748
- And I went ahead and made
some Khao Tom Mud--

37:52.792 --> 37:56.578
banana leaf sticky rice thing,
it's delish.

37:56.622 --> 37:59.059
Oh, but the dye still needs
to dry in the Chut Thais,

37:59.102 --> 38:02.192
so that'll take a minute.

38:02.236 --> 38:05.413
Yes, I am feeling much better.

38:05.457 --> 38:08.851
I just needed to
take control of the situation.

38:10.375 --> 38:12.377
[knock at door]

38:12.420 --> 38:14.640
Wait, can--I'm sorry,
can I call you back?

38:19.166 --> 38:21.299
- You called.

38:27.827 --> 38:29.307
May I?

38:30.656 --> 38:32.397
- Uh... yeah.

38:32.440 --> 38:33.789
Let me just grab you a plate.

38:33.833 --> 38:36.662
- I lived off of these
on Koh Samui.

38:39.012 --> 38:41.188
Where's your furniture?

38:41.231 --> 38:43.321
- It was stolen.

38:43.364 --> 38:44.931
- By whom?

38:44.974 --> 38:47.629
- Your target.

38:47.673 --> 38:49.544
Remember?

38:49.588 --> 38:51.981
Although, by this point, he's
gonna die of old age first.

38:52.025 --> 38:53.983
- I have other clients.

38:54.027 --> 38:57.378
- I am paying you
a lot of money.

39:02.296 --> 39:03.863
- For you.

39:06.735 --> 39:07.823
From Chile.

39:07.867 --> 39:09.390
I don't support
how they're made,

39:09.434 --> 39:12.219
but their little hands are...

39:12.262 --> 39:14.308
so precise.

39:17.398 --> 39:20.009
- Move me up on your schedule.

39:20.053 --> 39:22.360
- Try them on.

39:24.666 --> 39:26.233
- [sighs]

39:26.276 --> 39:28.409
You've done the leg work.

39:28.453 --> 39:31.281
- It's harder than I thought.

39:31.325 --> 39:32.892
- He is not hard to find.

39:32.935 --> 39:34.328
- He's not the problem.

39:34.372 --> 39:36.765
- Well, who is?
- You.

39:36.809 --> 39:38.811
- [sighs]

39:38.854 --> 39:40.856
- Stunning.

39:40.900 --> 39:42.815
All of it.

39:42.858 --> 39:45.034
- What?
- You're distracting.

39:45.078 --> 39:46.514
- How?

39:47.820 --> 39:50.431
- I can't stop thinking
about you.

39:51.693 --> 39:53.347
Mmm.

39:53.391 --> 39:55.915
[speaking Thai]

39:55.958 --> 39:57.743
And if I'm honest...

39:59.658 --> 40:02.487
That's why I've been
dragging my feet.

40:06.447 --> 40:08.014
- Well, what am
I supposed to do here?

40:08.057 --> 40:09.755
- Have dinner with me.

40:16.762 --> 40:18.720
- When did they get in?
- This morning.

40:18.764 --> 40:20.853
- DL Dave, too?
- The whole posse.

40:20.896 --> 40:21.897
- Is he pissed?

40:21.941 --> 40:22.898
- You charged a hot tub

40:22.942 --> 40:25.466
to the United States
government.

40:25.510 --> 40:27.163
- How do I look?
- Like you're gonna cry.

40:27.207 --> 40:28.077
- Well, I'm not.
- Don't.

40:28.121 --> 40:29.339
- I won't.

40:29.383 --> 40:30.297
- You haven't cried
in three days.

40:30.340 --> 40:32.342
- So?
- You're due.

40:32.386 --> 40:34.301
- I promise, okay?

40:35.781 --> 40:37.304
[crying]
They bought the place in cash,

40:37.347 --> 40:38.827
and they're selling 'em,
like, way below cost

40:38.871 --> 40:40.350
and the only way
that works is if the plan

40:40.394 --> 40:42.178
is to go out of business,
so before you send me home,

40:42.222 --> 40:44.572
just, like, please put
forensic accounting on it,

40:44.616 --> 40:47.314
'cause, I swear to God,
if I'm wrong about this,

40:47.357 --> 40:50.099
I will resign if this isn't the
best give I've ever given you.

40:50.143 --> 40:52.101
Just trust me.

40:52.145 --> 40:54.539
- What do you think, Dave?

40:54.582 --> 40:57.498
- No one is shipping you home.

40:57.542 --> 41:00.632
- Thank you.
- Let's get the team on it.

41:00.675 --> 41:01.894
- Yes.

41:01.937 --> 41:03.896
- There's a pattern here.
- Yes!

41:03.939 --> 41:06.333
- His car dealership
got busted, too.

41:06.376 --> 41:08.596
- Wait, sorry.
What?

41:08.640 --> 41:10.729
- Put a tail on this guy.

41:10.772 --> 41:12.905
- Guy?
Wait, wait.

41:12.948 --> 41:14.820
W-why is it the guy?

41:14.863 --> 41:17.387
- And, fellas...
let's tighten the net.

41:17.431 --> 41:20.652
Last time he got off
on a technicality.

41:20.695 --> 41:23.306
[Jerry Reed's
"I Feel for You"]

41:23.350 --> 41:25.613
- Let's get out of here.

41:25.657 --> 41:28.790
[indistinct chatter]

41:28.834 --> 41:30.705
[laughter]

41:30.749 --> 41:35.275
- ♪ To see you there
crying, boy ♪

41:35.318 --> 41:36.624
[door closes]

41:36.668 --> 41:38.539
- ♪ Brings to mind

41:38.583 --> 41:40.802
♪

41:40.846 --> 41:44.458
♪ All the things I told you

41:44.502 --> 41:46.416
♪ One time

41:46.460 --> 41:49.855
♪

41:51.726 --> 41:55.556
♪ Now sit there and cry, boy

41:55.600 --> 41:58.428
♪ The way that I did
one time ♪

41:58.472 --> 42:00.692
♪

42:00.735 --> 42:04.086
♪ And wish
you could die, boy ♪

42:04.130 --> 42:07.568
♪ To get that woman
off of your mind ♪

42:07.612 --> 42:09.570
♪

42:09.614 --> 42:13.705
♪ Go on and fall
all to pieces, son ♪

42:13.748 --> 42:20.146
♪ The way
that she made me do ♪

42:20.189 --> 42:24.803
♪ I know what you're going
through, and I feel... ♪
